				\begin{document}$$L = \kappa _{\mathrm{el}} / GT$$\end{document} is the Lorenz number. By introducing ZelT\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$Z_{\mathrm{el}}T$$\end{document}, the total figure of merit can be re-expressed as follows:3ZT=ZelT1+(κph/κel).\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
