				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$1 \times 1 \times 400$$\end{document} in x, y, and z directions, respectively, where z is the transport direction. The energy cutoff is chosen to be 150Ry\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$150\,\mathrm{Ry}$$\end{document}.Figure 1
(a) The device model of the anthracene molecule sandwiched between ZGNR leads. The edge carbon atoms of the anthracene molecule are substituted by (b) NB, (c) N, or (d) B atoms. Various parts of the sample and their corresponding dimension are indicated at the bottom of the figure.

